//axhob_operation
{bust_garrison_cygwin}

NOTE: {busn_garrison} ceremony with Cygwin bash as the workload shell,
for Windows nodes reached via Cygwin sshd.
Destructive: removes any prior workload account named
{burc_workload_user}
and recreates it from a clean slate.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and its
referenced {burn_regime} profile is reachable.

//axhoq_precondition
Cygwin sshd is installed on the node and {burp_privileged_user}
(member of the Administrators group) trusts {burp_privileged_key_file}
for key-only SSH (operator-bootstrapped out-of-band).

//axhoq_precondition
{burp_workload_key_file} is unencrypted and exists on the operator's
station.

//axhos_step
. *Open admin SSH*: connect as {burp_privileged_user} using
{burp_privileged_key_file}; key-auth only.

//axhos_step
. *Place admin trust*: idempotently install the admin pubkey
(derived via `ssh-keygen -y`) in admin's authorized_keys with the
shell-letter `c` `command=` directive from {bujb_jurisdiction}.

//axhos_step
. *Destroy workload*: remove any existing {burc_workload_user} Cygwin
account via the Cygwin user-management equivalent of `userdel -r`.

//axhos_step
. *Create workload*: provision {burc_workload_user} as an unprivileged,
ssh-only Cygwin account.

//axhos_step
. *Place workload trust*: write the workload pubkey
(derived via `ssh-keygen -y`) to the workload's authorized_keys with
the shell-letter `c` `command=` directive.

//axhos_step
. *Plant workload key*: copy {burp_workload_key_file} to the workload
account at the shell-letter `c` destination path hardcoded in
{bujb_jurisdiction}.

//axhos_step
. *Validate round-trip*: SSH as workload, run a no-op command, verify
exit 0.

//axhog_guarantee
On success the node has exactly one workload account named
{burc_workload_user} reachable via Cygwin bash.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the round-trip validation succeeds.
Non-zero on admin SSH failure, Cygwin account-management failure,
key-write failure, or workload validation failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_garrison_wsl}

NOTE: {busn_garrison} ceremony with WSL bash as the workload shell,
for Windows nodes reached via the WSL distribution `rbtww-main`
(hardcoded in {bujb_jurisdiction}).
Destructive: removes any prior workload account named
{burc_workload_user}
and recreates it from a clean slate.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and its
referenced {burn_regime} profile is reachable.

//axhoq_precondition
The default WSL distribution on the node is `rbtww-main` and its sshd
is installed; mismatch fails fast with a clear error.

//axhoq_precondition
{burp_privileged_user} (member of the Administrators group) trusts
{burp_privileged_key_file} for key-only SSH against the WSL distribution
(operator-bootstrapped out-of-band).

//axhoq_precondition
{burp_workload_key_file} is unencrypted and exists on the operator's
station.

//axhos_step
. *Open admin SSH*: connect as {burp_privileged_user} using
{burp_privileged_key_file}; key-auth only into the WSL distribution.

//axhos_step
. *Place admin trust*: idempotently install the admin pubkey
(derived via `ssh-keygen -y`) in admin's authorized_keys with the
shell-letter `w` `command=` directive from {bujb_jurisdiction}.

//axhos_step
. *Destroy workload*: remove any existing {burc_workload_user} account
inside the WSL distribution via `userdel -r`.

//axhos_step
. *Create workload*: provision {burc_workload_user} as an unprivileged,
ssh-only Linux account inside `rbtww-main`.

//axhos_step
. *Place workload trust*: write the workload pubkey
(derived via `ssh-keygen -y`) to the workload's authorized_keys with
the shell-letter `w` `command=` directive.

//axhos_step
. *Plant workload key*: copy {burp_workload_key_file} to the workload
account at the shell-letter `w` destination path hardcoded in
{bujb_jurisdiction}.

//axhos_step
. *Validate round-trip*: SSH as workload, run a no-op command, verify
exit 0.

//axhog_guarantee
On success the node has exactly one workload account named
{burc_workload_user} reachable via the WSL distribution `rbtww-main`.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the round-trip validation succeeds.
Non-zero on WSL distribution mismatch, admin SSH failure, account-
management failure, key-write failure, or workload validation failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_handbook_jurisdiction_top}

NOTE: Top-level landing surface for the {bus_jurisdiction} handbook.
Renders handbook prose to the operator's terminal as the entry point
into bootstrap, garrison, and dispatch procedures.
No remote contact and no profile mutation.

//axhos_step
. *Render landing*: emit the jurisdiction handbook landing content,
including pointers to the admin SSH bootstrap procedure (operator-
manual prerequisite to {busn_garrison}), the per-shell-letter
garrison tabtargets, and the workload dispatch tabtargets.

//axhog_guarantee
No remote contact occurred and no local file was written.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 after the landing content is printed.
Non-zero only when the handbook content cannot be located or rendered.

//axhob_operation
{bust_knock}

NOTE: Probes the workload account's reachability via key-only SSH.
Used to confirm that a {burp_investiture}'s workload trust is currently
usable before dispatching real work, and used internally as the
final-step validation of {busn_garrison}.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and its
referenced {burn_regime} profile is reachable.

//axhoq_precondition
{busn_garrison} has been run for this {burp_investiture} so that
{burc_workload_user} exists on the node and trusts the workload pubkey
derived from {burp_workload_key_file}.

//axhos_step
. *Open workload SSH*: connect as {burc_workload_user} using
{burp_workload_key_file}; key-auth only.

//axhos_step
. *Issue trivial command*: execute a no-op on the remote
(e.g., `true`) and observe the remote exit status.

//axhog_guarantee
No remote OS state was modified.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the remote command returns 0 within the probe window.
Non-zero on connection refusal, authentication failure, remote-exec
failure, or probe-window timeout.

